-- Russia's GDP could fall by 4.5 pct in 2015 if oil at $60/barrel - c.bank
-- By Alexander Winning
-- Mon Dec 15, 2014 10:08AM EST
-- None



MOSCOW, Dec 15 (Reuters) - Russia's gross domestic product could contract by around 4.5 percent in 2015 if oil prices are at $60 a barrel, the central bank said in a monetary policy document on Monday.     (Reporting by Alexander Winning; Writing by Polina Devitt; Editing by Lidia Kelly)  ((Polina.Devitt@thomsonreuters.com; +7 495 775 12 42; Reuters Messaging: polina.devitt.reuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: RUSSIA CBANK/

